Iran Needs $40 Billion to Develop Oil Fields, Newspaper Says

-- B y   A n d r e w   J .   B a r d e n
-- 
2011-08-07T05:56:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/iran-needs-40-billion-to-develop-oil-fields-newspaper-says.html
Iran  needs about $40 billion in this
Iranian calendar year to speed up the development of oil and gas
fields it shares with neighboring countries, Oil Minister Rostam
Qasemi said, according to the state-run  Iran  newspaper reported.  Iran will issue a “great volume of various bonds” in the
current year to help finance the projects, Qasemi was quoted as
saying in the report published in the Tehran-based daily
yesterday. The new Iranian year started on March 21st.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 